{
  "stem": "1062.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And from there I was marched to Auschwitz-- from Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And they lined us up on a-- on a-- you know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And they were driving us, they were driving us to Auschwitz which is the camp in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when I saw the sign there [SPEAKING GERMAN], I'll never forget, never forget.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "We came into that gate, and then we made a right turn.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I see the sign, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I speak Yiddish, I said, oh, if you work, you're going to-- you know, whatever it means.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And I felt a little better.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And we were in Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They lined us up one day.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] And everybody-- we all have our shoes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they took off our shoes, and they pulled off the heels from the shoes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "They pulled off the heels.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Because some people put in money into the heels.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "So they pulled off the heels from the shoes, and then they gave me other shoes.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "They gave me shoes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The shoes had wooden-- wooden soles with material on it, you know so.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And from there I was marched to a camp which is called Buna, Buna Monowitz.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "Today, Auschwitz is called Auschwitz-I.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "Birkenau is called Auschwitz-II, and Buna is called Auschwitz-III.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "Buna Monowitz one of it was a big factory which was an IG farm, IG farm from IG farm.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And they employed us as slave labor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And, you know, IG farm went to the SS, and they-- and they hired us as labor.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And apparently the SS got paid for us, to feed us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "Now, we were staying in Buna.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "In the morning, in Buna, you got up and first of all, we had barracks, you know And the barracks were bunks.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "They were three in a row, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And they had-- they had like barrels in the middle.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "First of all, when I was in Birkenau, they used to have like-- in the barrack, there was long stoves-- long stoves.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "About maybe 60, 70 feet long-- that was for heating purposes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Because at one time, that used to be for horses.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "On either side of the stove was a chimney.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "When you go back to Auschwitz, you don't see the chimney and those long stoves.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "But they used to use those stoves, what they used to do is they used to take somebody and put them in there, and then beat them.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "So the stove, I mean this long thing, would muffle the sound out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "But in Buna, we had barracks, regular barracks, because this was, you know-- IG farm had a factory, the Buna factory, where they made synthetic rubber.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "And in case you had to go at night to the bathroom, so you went to the barrel-- there were barrels lined up.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "And when the barrel was full, [LAUGHS] whoever was lucky enough, you know, then you had to take the barrel out, someplace out-- carry it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "It was heavy.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So some people did not go to the barrel, so-- [LAUGHS] so they peed them on top of the other.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the guy who was in the bottom, he got the worse part of it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So everybody want to stay on top, you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But this was-- but in Buna already it was different.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In Buna, there was already bathrooms, more or less.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in-- in-- in-- in-- in-- in there was one place where they had showers, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Once a week we go for showers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You could go for delousing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Delousing is you took off your clothes and you throw them in there, and-- and they boiled-- they boiled-- you know, they-- they boiled the-- the clothes.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And they gave them back to you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I'll tell you one thing-- in Auschwitz, in Buna, there were no lice.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You know, there were no-- you know, there was no-- they-- they kept pretty clean there.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The only problem is, you know, in Buna, whenever after a couple of weeks, they would come there for a selection.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In other words, there was come a doctor-- this doctor's name was, in Buna, his name was-- his name was Fisher.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they would take the whole block and line 'em up.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And whoever was too skinny, you know, they would take them out in the night.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And a couple of days later, they were sent to the gas chamber.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "My uncle was sent there, and other-- you know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And even there, I remember even there, when they-- when they-- when they had a selection to take them away to Auschwitz, and there was a rumor they're going to be gassed.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And there was one boy I knew, he says to me, they're going to go to a sanatorium in order to build us up a little bit.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Even then they wouldn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
